reviews.review_text:
Recorded chain was from my seats This appears to be master copy of the line I ran with two tapers from my seats. The two tapers were from the Boston area and one of them I had recorded with and patched out of in 1983. His name was Ross, I believe. I met up with them again in Philly and Ross and his friend were in the mist of combining their systems together. One had 300 the other had 421's. The mixer that was used was a Yamaha. We used my seat for all three nights since they were between the 14th and 8th row center. The first night we were just off the isle on the right.

Each night there were between 8 and 15 decks patched in. I'm really glad this copy has surfaced since my second set was recorded on a Memorex metal tape, which developed drop out over time. It is good to get clean copy. 

I checked out Steve's other two shows from this run and it appears that he patched out of another system. Too bad because I think you will notice amazing separation and details in this recording that further back does not capture. 

It just goes to show what a small world this is. I've seen Steve's name up here a number of times but could not put a face to him but apparently our paths have crossed.

Thanks guys!
